# EasySaving SwiftFormat configuration (task 0-3).
#
# Opinionated choices:
# 1. SwiftFormat owns formatting; SwiftLint owns everything else — see the
#    .swiftlint.yml header for the ownership split.
# 2. --swiftversion 6.2 lets rules apply Swift 6 idioms safely (matches the
#    package's tools version).
# 3. Everything else stays on defaults on purpose (4-space indent,
#    alphabetized imports): fewer deviations, less bikeshedding.

--swiftversion 6.2
--exclude .build,EasySavingKit/.build,fastlane
